content: I'm still hesitant to include KYC protocols as part of that.  It can create a system where wealthy people get to be anonymous and poor people who want to participate have to KYC.  It may be better for end users to disallow the KYC solution entirely so poor people aren't tempted into doxxing themselves.

author: emhane
content:
if you do find a reason for the overlays to overlap <@543900561460822016> (and then not doing the k-disjoint paths as it doesn't really gain anything), then upgrading the k-buckets to support overlays like shown below, will improve latency.
```rust
pub struct KBucket<TNodeId, TVal: Eq> {
    /// The nodes contained in the bucket.
    nodes: ArrayVec<Arc<RwLock<Node<TNodeId, TVal>>>, MAX_NODES_PER_BUCKET>,
```
if a node goes offline, all overlays will be aware of it, so only one overlay will lose the `request_time_out * (retries + 1)`  time on a query including a peer that goes offline.
